title: Number of imported live chickens to remain at about 30 000
content_text: The daily quantities of imported live chickens from the Mainland would remain at about 30 000 for the next two weeks, a spokesman for the Health, Welfare and Food Bureau said today (May 11). The importation of Mainland live chickens was resumed on April 20 on a pilot basis. The spokesman said: "We are satisfied with the testing results of the imported chickens during the pilot period. "From a public health point of view, the overcrowded conditions of our retail markets would make it undesirable
